<br>
Right now, I'm understand I'm being drafted into being the code god of either a very dark non-superhero mutant-type MUSH, or a modern WoD MUSH based on political intrigue and designed to force people out of hangout and clique RP. Neither of those have come to pass yet, though. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gyreredbranch>Gyre Redbranch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 212<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/10/03 9:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=249.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Any MUSH'ers/MUX'ers Out There?</span><hr size=1> I spent years playing (and then working for) a couple of commercial MUD's, Gemstone III and Dragonrealms.  Very good games, great player communities.<br>
